  "description": "A comprehensive book that emphasizes the major techniques, methods, and data sources of contemporary population studies. Written by a sociologist and a demographer, the book's principal aim is to improve the students' skills primarily as consumers and secondarily as producers of demographic information. One reviewer says, \"The author has a pleasant style. It is the voice of knowledge combined with a gentle voice of teaching.\" He goes on to say of the book, \"It is really unique and refreshingly original. It is comprehensive and comprehensible.\" -Ron Hammond, University of Utah. The book takes an applied interdisciplinary approach, emphasizing demographic resources such as software, data sets, journals, and the Internet. For anyone interested in population studies.",
